  "html": "<h1>Applies to</h1>\r\n  <ul>\r\n    <li>C&#43;&#43;</li>\r\n  </ul>\r\n  <h1>What to Check For</h1>\r\n  <p>Verify that exceptions are used instead of error codes whenever possible.</p>\r\n  <h1>Why</h1>\r\n  <p>Exceptions are more secure than error codes, because a program may ignore error codes and keep running, but unhandled exceptions make the program terminate, thus preventing unintended behavior.</p>\r\n  <h1>How to Check</h1>\r\n  <p>Review code and look for functions that return error codes. Consider whether it is possible to use exceptions instead of error codes.</p>\r\n  <h1>How to Fix</h1>\r\n  <p>Rewrite functions that return error codes to throw exceptions instead. Rewrite code that handles errors to use exception handling instead of checking error codes.</p>\r\n  <h1>Related Items</h1>\r\n  <ul>\r\n    <li>\r\n      <a href=\"/article/25d6522f-77d2-4f08-abee-88247a7b4118\">Use C&#43;&#43; Exceptions Where Possible</a>\r\n      <li>\r\n        <a href=\"/article/fa97587e-ddd5-4a30-a7f4-81c2bf24c91c\">Error codes are used when exceptions aren't possible</a>\r\n        <li>\r\n          <a href=\"/article/e4a3052e-13f2-4062-9a83-49185ff14b0a\">Centralize Error Handling</a>\r\n        </li>\r\n      </li>\r\n    </li>\r\n  </ul>"
